cards.text:
This spell costs {1} less to cast for each Citizen you control.
Flying
cards.flavor: Still and solemn as the statues of her kind that decorated the Park Heights rooftops, she gazed in sorrow on the city below.

cards.name: Backup Agent
cards.text: When Backup Agent enters the battlefield, put a +1/+1 counter on target creature.
cards.flavor: "My sources say the Beamtown Bullies were spotted in the Mezzio. Keep your eyes sharp and stay close to me."

cards.name: Ballroom Brawlers
cards.text: Whenever Ballroom Brawlers attacks, Ballroom Brawlers and up to one other target creature you control both gain your choice of first strike or lifelink until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Don't try to cut in. They'll cut back.

cards.name: Boon of Safety
cards.text:
Put a shield counter on target creature. (If that creature would be dealt damage or destroyed, remove a shield counter from it instead.)
Scry 1.
cards.flavor:
"Saving a stranger's life is an excellent recruitment method. Luckily, peril is so easy to come by."
-Falco Spara

cards.name: Brokers Initiate
cards.text: {4}{G/U}: Brokers Initiate has base power and toughness 5/5 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Regarding the relative might of pen and sword, the official position of the Brokers is "Why choose?"

cards.name: Buy Your Silence
cards.text: Exile target nonland permanent. Its controller creates a Treasure token. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
cards.flavor: Mikey "the Mouth" kept his nickname after he struck a deal with Gregorio, even though he never spoke another word.

cards.name: Celebrity Fencer
cards.text: Alliance - Whenever another creature enters the battlefield under your control, put a +1/+1 counter on Celebrity Fencer.
cards.flavor: After a brief but memorable incident at her first performance, she was never heckled again.

cards.name: Citizen's Crowbar
cards.text:
When Citizen's Crowbar enters the battlefield, create a 1/1 green and white Citizen creature token, then attach Citizen's Crowbar to it.
Equipped creature gets +1/+1 and has "{W}, {T}, Sacrifice Citizen's Crowbar: Destroy target artifact or enchantment."
Equip {2} ({2}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

cards.name: Dapper Shieldmate
cards.text:
Dapper Shieldmate enters the battlefield with a shield counter on it. (If it would be dealt damage or destroyed, remove a shield counter from it instead.)
As long as it's your turn, Dapper Shieldmate gets +2/+0.
cards.flavor: Descended from Old Capenna's paladins, the Brokers are masters of defensive combat.

cards.name: Depopulate
cards.text: Each player who controls a multicolored creature draws a card. Then destroy all creatures.
cards.flavor: No screams rang out. No blood stained the streets. In an instant, the bustling metropolis simply fell silent.

cards.name: Elspeth Resplendent
cards.text:
[+1]: Choose up to one target creature. Put a +1/+1 counter and a counter from among flying, first strike, lifelink, or vigilance on it.
[−3]: Look at the top seven cards of your library. You may put a permanent card with mana value 3 or less from among them onto the battlefield with a shield counter on it. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in a random order.
[−7]: Create five 3/3 white Angel creature tokens with flying.

cards.name: Extraction Specialist
cards.text:
Lifelink
When Extraction Specialist enters the battlefield, return target creature card with mana value 2 or less from your graveyard to the battlefield. That creature can't attack or block for as long as you control Extraction Specialist.

cards.name: Gathering Throng
cards.text: When Gathering Throng enters the battlefield, you may search your library for any number of cards named Gathering Throng, reveal them, put them into your hand, then shuffle.
cards.flavor: A plus-one is simply not enough.

cards.name: Giada, Font of Hope
cards.text:
Flying, vigilance
Each other Angel you control enters the battlefield with an additional +1/+1 counter on it for each Angel you already control.
{T}: Add {W}. Spend this mana only to cast an Angel spell.
cards.flavor: The source of the Cabaretti's Halo turned out to be a single teenage girl.

cards.name: Halo Fountain
cards.text:
{W}, {T}, Untap a tapped creature you control: Create a 1/1 green and white Citizen creature token.
{W}{W}, {T}, Untap two tapped creatures you control: Draw a card.
{W}{W}{W}{W}{W}, {T}, Untap fifteen tapped creatures you control: You win the game.

cards.name: Hold for Ransom
cards.text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature can't attack or block and has "{7}: Hold for Ransom's controller sacrifices it and draws a card. Activate only as a sorcery."
cards.flavor:
"Let's find out how much your friends think you're worth."
-Gino, hired kidnapper

cards.name: Illuminator Virtuoso
cards.text:
Double strike
Whenever Illuminator Virtuoso becomes the target of a spell you control, it connives. (Draw a card, then discard a card. If you discarded a nonland card, put a +1/+1 counter on this creature.)
cards.flavor: The Obscura reserve their keenest blades for traitors in their midst.

cards.name: Inspiring Overseer
cards.text:
Flying
When Inspiring Overseer enters the battlefield, you gain 1 life and draw a card.
cards.flavor:
"This city could certainly use a bit more divine intervention."
-Inspector Jillard

cards.name: Kill Shot
cards.text: Destroy target attacking creature.
cards.flavor:
"In the assassination trade, no one lives to make more than one mistake."
-Anhelo, the Painter

cards.name: Knockout Blow
cards.text:
This spell costs {2} less to cast if it targets a red creature.
Knockout Blow deals 4 damage to target attacking or blocking creature and you gain 2 life.
cards.flavor: "Subsequent efforts to deconstruct this facility will be punished with increasing severity."

cards.name: Mage's Attendant
cards.text: When Mage's Attendant enters the battlefield, create a 1/1 blue Wizard creature token with "{1}, Sacrifice this creature: Counter target noncreature spell unless its controller pays {1}."
cards.flavor: Crime sometimes makes unlikely allies into lifelong friends.

cards.name: Mysterious Limousine
cards.text:
Whenever Mysterious Limousine enters the battlefield or attacks, exile up to one other target creature until Mysterious Limousine leaves the battlefield. If a creature is put into exile this way, return each other card exiled with Mysterious Limousine to the battlefield under its owner's control.
Crew 2

cards.name: Patch Up
cards.text: Return up to three target creature cards with total mana value 3 or less from your graveyard to the battlefield.
cards.flavor: "Don't tell me who sent you or who you work for. The less I know, the better."

cards.name: Rabble Rousing
cards.text:
Hideaway 5 (When this enchantment enters the battlefield, look at the top five cards of your library, exile one face down, then put the rest on the bottom in a random order.)
Whenever you attack with one or more creatures, create that many 1/1 green and white Citizen creature tokens. Then if you control ten or more creatures, you may play the exiled card without paying its mana cost.

cards.name: Raffine's Guidance
cards.text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +1/+1.
You may cast Raffine's Guidance from your graveyard by paying {2}{W} rather than paying its mana cost.

cards.name: Raffine's Informant
cards.text: When Raffine's Informant enters the battlefield, it connives. (Draw a card, then discard a card. If you discarded a nonland card, put a +1/+1 counter on this creature.)
cards.flavor: "I've analyzed the vault schematic. Do you want the fast way, the easy way, or the secret way in?"

cards.name: Refuse to Yield
cards.text: Target creature gets +2/+7 until end of turn. Untap it.
cards.flavor: Her opponent threw her through the window, so she retaliated by throwing the window through her opponent.

cards.name: Revelation of Power
cards.text: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn. If it has a counter on it, it also gains flying and lifelink until end of turn.
cards.flavor: As Ob Nixilis closed in, Halo swept through Giada like an electrical current, and inside her, something long dormant unfurled its wings.

cards.name: Rumor Gatherer
cards.text: Alliance - Whenever another creature enters the battlefield under your control, scry 1. If this is the second time this ability has resolved this turn, draw a card instead.
cards.flavor: "It's delightful, the things their owners reveal when they think no one is listening."

cards.name: Sanctuary Warden
cards.text:
Flying
Sanctuary Warden enters the battlefield with two shield counters on it.
Whenever Sanctuary Warden enters the battlefield or attacks, you may remove a counter from a creature or planeswalker you control. If you do, draw a card and create a 1/1 green and white Citizen creature token.

cards.name: Sky Crier
cards.text:
Flying, lifelink
{3}{W}: You and target opponent each draw a card.
cards.flavor: "Breaking news! Lord Xander found dead! Suspect at large!"

cards.name: Speakeasy Server
cards.text:
Flying
When Speakeasy Server enters the battlefield, you gain 1 life for each other creature you control.
cards.flavor: "Whatever ails you, friends, this will cure it for tonight! And leave you with a little inspiration for tomorrow."

cards.name: Swooping Protector

Flash

Flying

cards.name: Backstreet Bruiser
cards.text:
Defender
As long as there are two or more counters among creatures you control, Backstreet Bruiser can attack as though it didn't have defender.
cards.flavor: "I could show you what's in the case, but it'd be the last thing you ever see."

cards.name: Brokers Veteran
cards.text: When Brokers Veteran dies, put a shield counter on target creature you control. (If that creature would be dealt damage or destroyed, remove a shield counter from it instead.)
cards.flavor: One last job before he retires.

cards.name: Case the Joint
cards.text: Draw two cards, then look at the top card of each player's library.
cards.flavor: Steel doors and iron bars are child's play for an Obscura operative.

cards.name: Cut Your Losses
cards.text:
Casualty 2 (As you cast this spell, you may sacrifice a creature with power 2 or greater. When you do, copy this spell and you may choose new targets for the copy.)
Target player mills half their library, rounded down.

cards.name: Disdainful Stroke
cards.text: Counter target spell with mana value 4 or greater.
cards.flavor:
"I've known for a year that you would cast this exact spell, at this exact spot, at this exact time."
-Raffine

cards.name: Echo Inspector
cards.text:
Flying
When Echo Inspector enters the battlefield, it connives. (Draw a card, then discard a card. If you discarded a nonland card, put a +1/+1 counter on this creature.)
cards.flavor: The rendezvous took place hours ago, but the Obscura agent read the residue with ease.

cards.name: Errant, Street Artist
cards.text:
Flash
Defender, haste
{1}{U}, {T}: Copy target spell you control that wasn't cast. You may choose new targets for the copy.
cards.flavor: Few know her face, but everyone knows her work.

cards.text:
This spell costs {U}{U}{U} less to cast if an opponent has drawn four or more cards this turn.
Draw X cards.
cards.flavor: Those who try to rob the Obscura often leave behind more than they take away.

cards.text: {1}{U}, Exile Expendable Lackey from your graveyard: Create a 1/1 blue Fish creature token with "This creature can't be blocked." Activate only as a sorcery.
cards.flavor:
"Altonio? No, I'm sorry. No one by that name works here."
-Raffine

cards.name: Faerie Vandal
cards.text:
Flash
Flying
Whenever you draw your second card each turn, put a +1/+1 counter on Faerie Vandal.
cards.flavor: "Greedy vault guard, wouldn't share. Now there's Halo in your hair!"

cards.text: {3}: Hypnotic Grifter connives. (Draw a card, then discard a card. If you discarded a nonland card, put a +1/+1 counter on this creature.)
cards.flavor: "All is calm. All is well. You know me to be a trusted member of your family, and I would like to discuss the contents of our safe."

cards.name: Ledger Shredder
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever a player casts their second spell each turn, Ledger Shredder connives. (Draw a card, then discard a card. If you discarded a nonland card, put a +1/+1 counter on this creature.)
cards.flavor: No evidence, no crime.

cards.text:
Casualty 1 (As you cast this spell, you may sacrifice a creature with power 1 or greater. When you do, copy this spell.)
Look at the top two cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the other on the bottom of your library.

cards.text:
Until end of turn, target artifact or creature becomes a 4/4 Angel artifact creature and gains flying.
Draw a card.
cards.flavor: New Capenna's statues hold Old Capenna's secrets.

Counter target spell unless its controller pays {2}.

cards.name: Obscura Initiate
cards.text:
Flying
{1}{W/B}: Obscura Initiate gains lifelink until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Obscura initiates are required to bring a gift of information. They are judged on both how useful it is and how hard it was to obtain.

cards.name: An Offer You Can't Refuse
cards.text: Counter target noncreature spell. Its controller creates two Treasure tokens. (They're artifacts with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
cards.flavor: Elspeth wanted answers. Xander needed a spy. Their paths were destined to cross.

cards.name: Out of the Way
cards.text:
This spell costs {2} less to cast if it targets a green permanent.
Return target nonland permanent an opponent controls to its owner's hand.
Draw a card.
cards.flavor: "You bore me."

Flash
When Psionic Snoop enters the battlefield, it connives. (Draw a card, then discard a card. If you discarded a nonland card, put a +1/+1 counter on this creature.)
cards.flavor: She knows your next move before you do.

cards.text: When Psychic Pickpocket enters the battlefield, it connives. When it connives this way, return up to one target nonland permanent to its owner's hand. (To have a creature connive, draw a card, then discard a card. If you discarded a nonland card, put a +1/+1 counter on that creature.)

cards.name: Public Enemy
cards.text:
Enchant creature
All creatures attack enchanted creature's controller each combat if able.
When enchanted creature dies, draw a card.
cards.flavor: Every Halo smuggler walks a razor's edge between untold riches and sudden disaster.

cards.name: Reservoir Kraken
cards.text:
Trample, ward {2}
At the beginning of each combat, if Reservoir Kraken is untapped, any opponent may tap an untapped creature they control. If they do, tap Reservoir Kraken and create a 1/1 blue Fish creature token with "This creature can't be blocked."

cards.name: Rooftop Nuisance
cards.text:
Casualty 1 (As you cast this spell, you may sacrifice a creature with power 1 or greater. When you do, copy this spell and you may choose new targets for the copy.)
Tap target creature. It doesn't untap during its controller's next untap step.
Draw a card.

cards.name: Run Out of Town
cards.text: The owner of target nonland permanent puts it on the top or bottom of their library.
cards.flavor: Better to depart in haste than be dearly departed.

cards.name: Security Bypass
cards.text:
Enchant creature
As long as enchanted creature is attacking alone, it can't be blocked.
Enchanted creature has "Whenever this creature deals combat damage to a player, it connives." (Its controller draws a card, then discards a card. If they discarded a nonland card, they put a +1/+1 counter on this creature.)

cards.name: Sewer Crocodile
cards.text: {3}{U}: Sewer Crocodile can't be blocked this turn. This ability costs {3} less to activate if there are five or more mana values among cards in your graveyard.
cards.flavor:
"Quick, let's hide in the sewer!"
-Ginsi the Thief, now deceased

cards.name: Sleep with the Fishes
cards.text:
Enchant creature
When Sleep with the Fishes enters the battlefield, tap enchanted creature and you create a 1/1 blue Fish creature token with "This creature can't be blocked."
Enchanted creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step.

cards.name: Slip Out the Back
cards.text: Put a +1/+1 counter on target creature. It phases out. (Treat it and anything attached to it as though they don't exist until your next turn.)
cards.flavor: "I was never here."

cards.text:
Wingshield Agent enters the battlefield with a shield counter on it. (If it would be dealt damage or destroyed, remove a shield counter from it instead.)
Whenever Wingshield Agent attacks, up to one other target creature gains flying until end of turn.

Hideaway 5 (When this enchantment enters the battlefield, look at the top five cards of your library, exile one face down, then put the rest on the bottom in a random order.)
Whenever you draw your first card during each of your draw steps, draw a card. Then if you have nine or more cards in hand, you may play the exiled card without paying its mana cost.

cards.name: Witness Protection
cards.text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature loses all abilities and is a green and white Citizen creature with base power and toughness 1/1 named Legitimate Businessperson. (It loses all other colors, card types, creature types, and names.)

cards.name: Angel of Suffering
cards.text:
Flying
If damage would be dealt to you, prevent that damage and mill twice that many cards.
cards.flavor: "If you wish for blessings, mortal, ask your demon masters. We've given enough to your kind."

cards.name: Body Launderer
cards.text:
Deathtouch
Whenever another nontoken creature you control dies, Body Launderer connives.
When Body Launderer dies, return another target non-Rogue creature card with equal or lesser power from your graveyard to the battlefield.

cards.name: Cemetery Tampering
cards.text:
Hideaway 5 (When this enchantment enters the battlefield, look at the top five cards of your library, exile one face down, then put the rest on the bottom in a random order.)
At the beginning of your upkeep, you may mill three cards. Then if there are twenty or more cards in your graveyard, you may play the exiled card without paying its mana cost.

cards.name: Corrupt Court Official
cards.text: When Corrupt Court Official enters the battlefield, target opponent discards a card.
cards.flavor:
"I wouldn't call what they have here a justice system. More like an auction."
-Elspeth

cards.name: Crooked Custodian
cards.text: Crooked Custodian enters the battlefield tapped.
cards.flavor: "Nothing to see here. Just carrying a carpet. Yes, the carpet wears boots. Stop asking questions."

cards.name: Cut of the Profits
cards.text:
Casualty 3 (As you cast this spell, you may sacrifice a creature with power 3 or greater. When you do, copy this spell.)
You draw X cards and you lose X life.
cards.flavor: Everybody is worth their weight in gold.

cards.name: Cutthroat Contender
cards.text: Pay 1 life: Cutthroat Contender gets +1/+0 until end of turn. Activate only once each turn.
cards.flavor: The fights may sometimes be rigged, but the front-row spectators know the wounds are real.

cards.name: Deal Gone Bad
cards.text: Target creature gets -3/-3 until end of turn. Target player mills three cards. (They put the top three cards of their library into their graveyard.)
cards.flavor:
"Feed the rumor mills with delicious treachery. Bad blood between those two is a good deal for us."
-Kamiz, Obscura Oculus

cards.name: Demon's Due
cards.text: Scry 2, then draw two cards. You lose 2 life.
cards.flavor: Ob Nixilis extends his hand not in partnership, but to affirm your subservience.

cards.text:
Casualty 1 (As you cast this spell, you may sacrifice a creature with power 1 or greater. When you do, copy this spell and you may choose new targets for the copy.)
Mill two cards, then you may return a creature card from your graveyard to your hand. (To mill a card, a player puts the top card of their library into their graveyard.)

cards.text:

When Dusk Mangler enters the battlefield, each opponent sacrifices a creature, discards a card, and loses 4 life.

cards.text:
Choose one -
• Target opponent reveals their hand. You may choose a creature, enchantment, or planeswalker card from it. That player discards that card.
• Target opponent sacrifices an enchantment.

cards.text: Until end of turn, target creature gets +2/+0 and gains "When this creature dies, return it to the battlefield tapped under its owner's control and you create a Treasure token." (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")

Blitz {3}{B} (If you cast this spell for its blitz cost, it gains haste and "When this creature dies, draw a card." Sacrifice it at the beginning of the next end step.)

This spell has flash as long as there are five or more mana values among cards in your graveyard.
Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
cards.flavor: "Up and at 'em, buddy. We've got more work to do."

cards.text:

Choose target creature or planeswalker. If it was dealt noncombat damage this turn, Grisly Sigil deals 3 damage to it and you gain 3 life. Otherwise, Grisly Sigil deals 1 damage to it and you gain 1 life.

cards.name: Illicit Shipment
cards.text:
Casualty 3 (As you cast this spell, you may sacrifice a creature with power 3 or greater. When you do, copy this spell and you may choose new targets for the copy.)
Search your library for a card, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
cards.flavor: Whatever the Maestros had ordered, it wasn't anyone's business, including his.

cards.name: Incriminate
cards.text: Choose two target creatures controlled by the same player. That player sacrifices one of them.
cards.flavor:
"If I were you, I'd check that elf's coat. I saw him slipping something into his pocket just before you arrived."
-Krandal, freelance instigator

cards.name: Join the Maestros
cards.text:
Casualty 2 (As you cast this spell, you may sacrifice a creature with power 2 or greater. When you do, copy this spell and you may choose new targets for the copy.)
Create a 4/3 black Ogre Warrior creature token.
cards.flavor: "We're family now, big guy."

cards.name: Maestros Initiate
cards.text: {4}{U/R}, Exile Maestros Initiate from your graveyard: Draw two cards, then discard a card.
cards.flavor:
"How far are you willing to go for your family, cleanblade?"
-Lord Xander

cards.name: Midnight Assassin
cards.text: Flying, deathtouch
cards.flavor: The broad avenues and graceful spires of Park Heights are the playground of the affluent. After nightfall, they also make a fine hunting ground.

cards.name: Murder
cards.text: Destroy target creature.
cards.flavor: Ob Nixilis decided the fastest way to seize control of New Capenna would be to usurp the networks of power already hidden there. Xander's Maestros were the first to fall.

Blitz {2}{B} (If you cast this spell for its blitz cost, it gains haste and "When this creature dies, draw a card." Sacrifice it at the beginning of the next end step.)

cards.text: For each color, return up to one target creature card of that color from your graveyard to your hand.
cards.flavor: Between the five of them, they'd committed every crime on the books and invented a few new ones.

Menace, lifelink
{1}, Sacrifice another creature: Look at the top card of your library. You may put that card into your graveyard.

cards.text: If your life total is less than your starting life total, this spell costs {X} less to cast, where X is the difference.
cards.flavor:
"Build your towers as tall as you want. The shadow always reaches higher."
-Message scrawled on an alley wall

cards.name: Shakedown Heavy
cards.text:
Menace
Whenever Shakedown Heavy attacks, defending player may have you draw a card. If they do, untap Shakedown Heavy and remove it from combat.
cards.flavor: "Look, we both get what we want. I get your Halo. You get to keep your kneecaps."

cards.text: {T}, Pay 3 life: Flip a coin. If you win the flip, you gain 6 life.
cards.flavor: "Only a chump stops after one unlucky loss. You're not a chump, are you?"

cards.name: Vampire Scrivener
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever you gain life during your turn, put a +1/+1 counter on Vampire Scrivener.
Whenever you lose life during your turn, put a +1/+1 counter on Vampire Scrivener.
cards.flavor: No one remains on her list for long.

Target creature gets -4/-4 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: "It's just business. You understand."

cards.name: Antagonize

cards.flavor:
"The little guy had guts at least. You can see 'em right there between those cobbles."
-Glunk, freelance crusher

cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, discard a card.
Draw two cards and create two Treasure tokens. (They're artifacts with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
cards.flavor: "Unimaginable riches? I assure you, I have a vivid imagination."
